Business magnate, Alhaji Aliko Dangote, has tested negative for the dreaded coronavirus. He disclosed this via his verified Twitter handle on Sunday. Dangote, and some governors, had been reported to have met with the Chief of Staff to the President, Abba Kyari, who tested positive for the virus. “The COVID-19 pandemic has significantly disrupted modern society, affecting our collective health and well-being,” he tweeted. He added, “As a global citizen and business leader, I took the COVID-19 test and the result came back NEGATIVE. “Coalition Against COVID-19 is an initiative that I am leading with other private sector leaders and our common goal is to support ongoing Government initiatives with our resources in the fight against COVID-19. “We are in this together and I am optimistic we will overcome.” 